column5: well got the new boat attached to my newly upgraded wheels ready to hit the bay tomorrow for bass wish me luck
i have it so it goes 32 kmph
Lmao nice setup, throw some mud tires and a lift kit and you have a back lake specialty vehicle LOL

well finished riggin it out and took it out a few times and hit frenchman's bay and got a bunch of bass both large and smallies biggest was a 6 lb bucket mouth no photos as i was to afraid to take any camera/phone with me lol
....... How do you afford to fuel that beast!
Plugs it into his neighbours outlet!  G
Post your mileage for the Dodge guys
well its 60 volts runs at 30km an hour and will go for about 30 km on a single charge pulling the kayak charging it costs me zip as hydro is included where i live
